  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nHi, \r\nThe `find()` family of methods in `ReactivePanacheMongoRepositoryBase` does not provide the `FindOptions` parameter. It only has the `Sort` option.\r\n\r\n```java\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(String query, Object... params);\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(String query, Sort sort, Object... params);\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(String query, Map<String, Object> params);\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(String query, Sort sort, Map<String, Object> params);\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(String query, Parameters params);\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(String query, Sort sort, Parameters params);\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(Document query);\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(Document query, Document sort);\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think is it possible to add a method like this:\r\n```java\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(String query, FindOptions findOptions, Object... params);\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(String query, FindOptions findOptions, Map<String, Object> params);\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(String query, FindOptions findOptions, Parameters params);\r\nReactivePanacheQuery<Entity> find(Document query, FindOptions findOptions);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\n_No response_",
